Class C_RandomInNormalDistrib

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.Random
      • simmasto0.util.C_RandomInNormalDistrib
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    I_ConstantNumeric, java.io.Serializable
    public class C_RandomInNormalDistrib
extends java.util.Random
implements I_ConstantNumeric
    An extension of java.util.Random, which adds methods to generate random numbers in normal distribution given a specific mean or both a mean and a standard deviation.
    Author:
    kyle wagner, elyk@acm.org Version 1.0, Sat Feb 3 18:38:23 2001

    • Method Detail

      • nextGaussian

        public double nextGaussian​(double mean)
        Simply relies on Random's nextGaussian(), but adds mean to it. Standard deviation of the result is 1.0.
        Parameters:
        mean - the mean of the normal distribution
        Returns:
        any legal double, but values will be generated under a normal (gaussian) distribution.

      • nextGaussian

        public double nextGaussian​(double mean,
                           double standDev)
        Simply relies on Random's nextGaussian(), but multiplies by standDev and adds mean to it. Standard deviation of the result is given by standDev.
        Parameters:
        mean - the mean of the normal distribution
        standDev - the standard deviation of the normal distribution
        Returns:
        any legal double, but values will be generated under a normal (gaussian) distribution.
